The paper deals with the task of retrieving similar images based on their shape, which is a common problem in computer vision and graphics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a fusion-based approach that combines multiple features to improve shape recognition, which is a common theme in the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics). Additionally, the paper uses a weighted ranking algorithm to find similarities among shapes, which is a common technique in the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves feature extraction and similarity search, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
